JOHANNESBURG - Trade union federation Cosatu has tabled a plan to save Eskom, involving a multi-billion investment from the government into the utility. READ: Ramaphosa defends Eskom CEO's appointment Cosatu has suggested the Public Investment Corporation invests billions in Eskom and stated its affiliated unions are in agreement with the plan. READ: Cosatu pledges support for ANC investment proposal Cosatu's parliamentary coordinator, Matthew Parks said, "Eskom is not just any state-owned enterprise in the country. "It's the most important single SOE we have. If it collapses, 12 million jobs in South Africa will be at risk," he said.